content.com/u/1537529?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mwhitneysdsu","html_url":"https://github.com/mwhitneysdsu","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mwhitneysdsu/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mwhitneysdsu/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mwhitneysdsu/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mwhitneysdsu/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mwhitneysdsu/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mwhitneysdsu/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mwhitneysdsu/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mwhitneysdsu/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mwhitneysdsu/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2014-11-12T16:04:18Z","updated_at":"2014-11-12T16:04:18Z","body":"I agree that it might be a \"sleeper\". At first it looks easy, but then I started thinking about other things. For example, if the site doesn't have en-us, I would still be happy with en, if it exists, or really en-anything, vs. getting de-de (German) or pt-br (Brazilian Portuguese).\n\nThis lead me down the path of considering a structure along the lines of language/region (e.g. en/us or pt/br) with fallback to the language directory if the region directory did not exist (or the line did not exist in the region file).\n\nAnother issue was that, for example, some regions may overlap, or even present an additional level to the hierarchy. For example, one of the languages available in Bonfire is properly represented by the language tag `es-419`, which is \"Spanish as used in Latin America\" (http://www.w3.org/International/articles/language-tags/), which would be appropriate for many of the countries which use Spanish as their primary language, but not for Spain itself (unless there are no other options).\n\nI didn't pursue it further 